<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-5976] RequestChannel.sendReponse records incorrect size for NetworkSend with TRACE logging</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5976</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In RequestChannel.scala, RequestChannel.sendResponse records incorrect size for `NetworkSend` when trace logging is enabled, as shown below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;RequestChannel.scala&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def sendResponse(response: RequestChannel.Response) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (isTraceEnabled) {
      val requestHeader = response.request.header
      trace(s&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Sending ${requestHeader.apiKey} response to client ${requestHeader.clientId} of &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + s&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;${response.responseSend.size} bytes.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;`responseSend` is of `scala.Option` type so it should be `response.responseSend.get.size`. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
